description:
This table `EUtranCellFDD` stores configuration parameters for FDD-LTE cells.

- `dateTime`: Timestamp of the configuration data.
- `Area_Name`: Name of the geographical area where the cell is located.
- `CellId`: Unique identifier for the cell.
- `Id2`: Duplicate of CellId.
- `Id3`:  Alternative identifier for the cell, potentially referencing different components.
- `vsDataType`: Data type identifier.
- `vsDataFormatVersion`: Version of the data format.
- `EUtranCellFDD.ns05LowBandSchedMode`: Scheduling mode for low-band in NS05.
- `EUtranCellFDD.tPollRetxRrcReleaseDl`: DL RRC release polling retransmission timer.
- `EUtranCellFDD.upperLayerAutoConfEnabled`: Flag indicating if upper layer auto-configuration is enabled.
- `EUtranCellFDD.cceDynUeAdmCtrlOverloadThr`: Overload threshold for dynamic UE admission control using CCEs.
- `EUtranCellFDD.aiAdvCellSupMode`: Mode for advanced inter-cell interference coordination.
- `EUtranCellFDD.dynUeAdmCtrlEnabled`: Flag indicating if dynamic UE admission control is enabled.
- `EUtranCellFDD.outOfCoverageThreshold`: Threshold for out-of-coverage conditions.
- `EUtranCellFDD.optimizedPdcchCongestThres`: Optimized PDCCH congestion threshold.
- `EUtranCellFDD.freqBand`: Frequency band of the cell.
- `EUtranCellFDD.plmn1AbConfProfileRef`: Reference to the access barring configuration profile for PLMN 1.
- `EUtranCellFDD.ttiBundlingAfterHo`: TTI bundling behavior after handover.
- `EUtranCellFDD.cellCapMaxCellSubCap`: Maximum cell capacity.
- `EUtranCellFDD.loadBasedCaEnabled`: Flag indicating if load-based carrier aggregation is enabled.
- `EUtranCellFDD.servOrPrioIFHoSetupBearer`: Flag for service or priority-based inter-frequency handover bearer setup.
- `EUtranCellFDD.rtpTimeout`: RTP timeout value.
- `EUtranCellFDD.iflbAbEnabled`: Flag indicating if inter-frequency load balancing access barring is enabled.
- `EUtranCellFDD.uncertSemiMajor`: Semi-major axis of the cell's uncertainty ellipse.
- `EUtranCellFDD.pagingPriorityDiffThr`: Paging priority difference threshold.
- `EUtranCellFDD.lbabBarringPriorityLevel`: Load balancing access barring priority level.
- `EUtranCellFDD.eabThreshRejRateLteHighBr`: EAB threshold rejection rate for LTE high bitrate.
- `EUtranCellFDD.eabThreshTimeHigh`: EAB threshold time for high bitrate.
- `EUtranCellFDD.eabPresenceBr`: EAB presence for broad range.
- `EUtranCellFDD.sCellHandlingAtVolteCall`: Handling of secondary cells during VoLTE calls.
- `EUtranCellFDD.measGapPattern`: Measurement gap pattern.
- `EUtranCellFDD.eDrxAllowed`: Flag indicating if enhanced DRX is allowed.
- `EUtranCellFDD.covTriggerdBlindHoAllowed`: Flag indicating if coverage-triggered blind handover is allowed.
- `EUtranCellFDD.prsConfigIndex`: Index of the Positioning Reference Signal (PRS) configuration.
- `EUtranCellFDD.acBarringForMoData`: Access barring configuration for mobile-originated data.
- `EUtranCellFDD.ulHeavyUeDetectEnabled`: Flag indicating if uplink heavy UE detection is enabled.
- `EUtranCellFDD.rachNoOfAllocationsPerFrame`: Number of RACH allocations per frame.
- `EUtranCellFDD.ulCatmEssShare`: Uplink Cat-M1 enhanced shared resources.
- `EUtranCellFDD.additionalPlmnReservedList`: Flag indicating if additional PLMNs are reserved.
- `EUtranCellFDD.eranUlCompUserSelSinrThr`: SINR threshold for E-UTRAN uplink user selection.
- `EUtranCellFDD.ttiBundlingAtSetup`: TTI bundling behavior at setup.
- `EUtranCellFDD.ulChannelBandwidth`: Uplink channel bandwidth.

- `EUtranCellFDD.highestSupportedCeLevelBr`: Highest supported cell edge level for broad range.
